tests.name: dict-append-1.0
tests.script:
# Test: dict append - basic
set d [dict create a hello]
puts [dict append d a " world"]
puts $d

tests.name: dict-append-1.1
tests.script:
# Test: dict append - new key
set d [dict create]
puts [dict append d newkey value]
puts $d

tests.name: dict-append-1.2
tests.script:
# Test: dict append - multiple strings
set d [dict create a x]
puts [dict append d a y z]
puts $d

tests.name: dict-create-1.0
tests.script:
# Test: dict create - basic creation
puts [dict create]
puts [dict create a 1]
puts [dict create a 1 b 2]
puts [dict create a 1 b 2 c 3]
tests.stdout:
a 1
a 1 b 2
a 1 b 2 c 3

tests.name: dict-create-1.1
tests.script:
# Test: dict create - special characters in keys/values
puts [dict create "key with spaces" "value with spaces"]
puts [dict create {key{brace}} {val{brace}}]
puts [dict create "a\tb" "c\nd"]

tests.name: dict-create-1.2
tests.script:
# Test: dict create - duplicate keys (last value wins)
puts [dict create a 1 a 2]
puts [dict create a 1 b 2 a 3]

tests.name: dict-error-1.0
tests.script:
# Test: dict - wrong number of args
catch {dict} err
puts $err

tests.name: dict-error-1.1
tests.script:
# Test: dict - unknown subcommand
catch {dict unknown arg} err
puts $err
tests.stdout: unknown or ambiguous subcommand "unknown": must be append, create, exists, filter, for, get, getdef, getwithdefault, incr, info, keys, lappend, map, merge, remove, replace, set, size, unset, update, values, or with

tests.name: dict-error-1.2
tests.script:
# Test: dict create - odd number of args
catch {dict create a} err
puts $err
tests.stdout: wrong # args: should be "dict create ?key value ...?"

tests.name: dict-error-1.3
tests.script:
# Test: dict - not a valid dict
catch {dict size "a b c"} err
puts $err
tests.stdout: missing value to go with key

tests.name: dict-error-1.4
tests.script:
# Test: dict incr - non-integer value
set d [dict create a hello]
catch {dict incr d a} err
puts $err

tests.name: dict-exists-1.0
tests.script:
# Test: dict exists - basic checks
set d [dict create a 1 b 2]
puts [dict exists $d a]
puts [dict exists $d b]
puts [dict exists $d c]

tests.name: dict-exists-1.1
tests.script:
# Test: dict exists - nested path
set d [dict create outer [dict create inner value]]
puts [dict exists $d outer]
puts [dict exists $d outer inner]
puts [dict exists $d outer missing]
puts [dict exists $d missing inner]

tests.name: dict-filter-1.0
tests.script:
# Test: dict filter key - basic pattern matching
set d [dict create apple 1 banana 2 apricot 3 cherry 4]
puts [dict filter $d key a*]
puts [dict filter $d key *a*]

tests.name: dict-filter-1.1
tests.script:
# Test: dict filter value - basic pattern matching
set d [dict create a red b green c blue d red]
puts [dict filter $d value red]
puts [dict filter $d value *e*]
tests.stdout:
a red d red
a red b green c blue d red

tests.name: dict-filter-1.2
tests.script:
# Test: dict filter script - basic
set d [dict create a 1 b 2 c 3 d 4]
puts [dict filter $d script {k v} {expr {$v > 2}}]

tests.name: dict-filter-1.3
dict-filter-1.4
tests.script:
# Test: dict filter key - multiple patterns
set d [dict create apple 1 banana 2 apricot 3 cherry 4]
puts [dict filter $d key a* c*]

tests.name: dict-for-1.0
dict-for-1.1
dict-for-1.2
tests.script:
# Test: dict for - break
set d [dict create a 1 b 2 c 3 d 4]
dict for {k v} $d {
    puts "$k=$v"
    if {$k eq "b"} break
}
puts "after break"

tests.name: dict-for-1.3
dict-for-1.4
dict-get-1.0
tests.script:
# Test: dict get - basic retrieval
set d [dict create a 1 b 2 c 3]
puts [dict get $d a]
puts [dict get $d b]
puts [dict get $d c]

tests.name: dict-get-1.1
tests.script:
# Test: dict get - no keys returns all pairs
set d [dict create a 1 b 2]
puts [dict get $d]

tests.name: dict-get-1.2
tests.script:
# Test: dict get - nested dictionary access
set d [dict create outer [dict create inner value]]
puts [dict get $d outer inner]
puts [dict get $d outer]

tests.name: dict-get-1.3
tests.script:
# Test: dict get - error on missing key
set d [dict create a 1]
catch {dict get $d nonexistent} err
puts $err

tests.name: dict-getdef-1.0
tests.script:
# Test: dict getdef - basic with existing key
set d [dict create a 1 b 2]
puts [dict getdef $d a default]
puts [dict getdef $d b default]

tests.name: dict-getdef-1.1
tests.script:
# Test: dict getdef - missing key returns default
set d [dict create a 1]
puts [dict getdef $d missing default]
puts [dict getdef $d another "not found"]

tests.name: dict-getdef-1.2
tests.script:
# Test: dict getdef - nested path
set d [dict create outer [dict create inner value]]
puts [dict getdef $d outer inner default]
puts [dict getdef $d outer missing default]

tests.name: dict-getwithdefault-1.0
tests.script:
# Test: dict getwithdefault - alias for getdef
set d [dict create a 1]
puts [dict getwithdefault $d a default]
puts [dict getwithdefault $d missing default]

tests.name: dict-incr-1.0
tests.script:
# Test: dict incr - basic increment
set d [dict create count 5]
puts [dict incr d count]
puts $d

tests.name: dict-incr-1.1
tests.script:
# Test: dict incr - with explicit increment
set d [dict create count 5]
puts [dict incr d count 10]
puts [dict incr d count -3]
puts $d

tests.name: dict-incr-1.2
tests.script:
# Test: dict incr - new key starts at 0
set d [dict create]
puts [dict incr d newkey]
puts [dict incr d another 5]
puts $d

tests.name: dict-info-1.0
tests.script:
# Test: dict info - returns implementation info
set d [dict create a 1 b 2 c 3]
set info [dict info $d]
puts [expr {[string length $info] > 0}]

tests.name: dict-keys-1.0
tests.script:
# Test: dict keys - basic
set d [dict create a 1 b 2 c 3]
puts [dict keys $d]

tests.name: dict-keys-1.1
tests.script:
# Test: dict keys - with pattern
set d [dict create apple 1 banana 2 apricot 3 cherry 4]
puts [dict keys $d]
puts [dict keys $d a*]
puts [dict keys $d *a*]
tests.stdout:
apple banana apricot cherry
apple apricot
apple banana apricot

tests.name: dict-keys-1.2
tests.script:
# Test: dict keys - empty dict
puts [dict keys {}]

tests.name: dict-lappend-1.0
tests.script:
# Test: dict lappend - basic
set d [dict create items {a b}]
puts [dict lappend d items c]
puts $d
tests.stdout:
items {a b c}
items {a b c}

tests.name: dict-lappend-1.1
tests.script:
# Test: dict lappend - new key
set d [dict create]
puts [dict lappend d newlist x y z]
puts $d
tests.stdout:
newlist {x y z}
newlist {x y z}

tests.name: dict-lappend-1.2
tests.script:
# Test: dict lappend - no values
set d [dict create items {a b c}]
puts [dict lappend d items]
puts $d
tests.stdout:
items {a b c}
items {a b c}

tests.name: dict-map-1.0
tests.script:
# Test: dict map - basic transformation
set d [dict create a 1 b 2 c 3]
puts [dict map {k v} $d {expr {$v * 2}}]

tests.name: dict-map-1.1
tests.script:
# Test: dict map - empty dict
puts [dict map {k v} {} {expr {$v * 2}}]

tests.name: dict-map-1.2
dict-map-1.3
dict-merge-1.0
tests.script:
# Test: dict merge - basic
puts [dict merge]
puts [dict merge {a 1}]
puts [dict merge {a 1} {b 2}]
puts [dict merge {a 1 b 2} {c 3 d 4}]
tests.stdout:
a 1
a 1 b 2
a 1 b 2 c 3 d 4

tests.name: dict-merge-1.1
tests.script:
# Test: dict merge - overlapping keys (last wins)
puts [dict merge {a 1 b 2} {b 20 c 3}]
puts [dict merge {a 1} {a 2} {a 3}]

tests.name: dict-order-1.0
tests.script:
# Test: dict preserves insertion order
set d [dict create z 1 a 2 m 3]
puts [dict keys $d]
dict set d b 4
puts [dict keys $d]
tests.stdout:
z a m
z a m b

tests.name: dict-remove-1.0
tests.script:
# Test: dict remove - basic
set d [dict create a 1 b 2 c 3]
puts [dict remove $d b]
puts [dict remove $d a c]
puts [dict remove $d]
tests.stdout:
a 1 c 3
b 2
a 1 b 2 c 3

tests.name: dict-remove-1.1
tests.script:
# Test: dict remove - nonexistent key (no error)
set d [dict create a 1 b 2]
puts [dict remove $d nonexistent]
puts [dict remove $d a nonexistent b]

tests.name: dict-replace-1.0
tests.script:
# Test: dict replace - basic
set d [dict create a 1 b 2]
puts [dict replace $d b 20]
puts [dict replace $d c 3]
puts [dict replace $d a 10 b 20 c 30]
tests.stdout:
a 1 b 20
a 1 b 2 c 3
a 10 b 20 c 30

tests.name: dict-replace-1.1
tests.script:
# Test: dict replace - no changes
set d [dict create a 1 b 2]
puts [dict replace $d]

tests.name: dict-replace-1.2
tests.script:
# Test: dict replace - error on odd args
catch {dict replace {a 1} b} err
puts $err
tests.stdout: wrong # args: should be "dict replace dictionary ?key value ...?"

tests.name: dict-set-1.0
tests.script:
# Test: dict set - basic set
set d [dict create a 1]
puts [dict set d b 2]
puts $d

tests.name: dict-set-1.1
tests.script:
# Test: dict set - update existing key
set d [dict create a 1 b 2]
puts [dict set d a 10]
puts $d

tests.name: dict-set-1.2
tests.script:
# Test: dict set - nested key path
set d [dict create]
puts [dict set d a b c value]
puts [dict get $d a b c]

tests.name: dict-set-1.3
tests.script:
# Test: dict set - create variable if not exists
unset -nocomplain newvar
dict set newvar key value
puts $newvar

tests.name: dict-size-1.0
tests.script:
# Test: dict size - basic
puts [dict size {}]
puts [dict size {a 1}]
puts [dict size {a 1 b 2 c 3}]

tests.name: dict-unset-1.0
tests.script:
# Test: dict unset - basic
set d [dict create a 1 b 2 c 3]
puts [dict unset d b]
puts $d

tests.name: dict-unset-1.1
tests.script:
# Test: dict unset - nested key path
set d [dict create outer [dict create inner1 a inner2 b]]
puts [dict unset d outer inner1]
puts $d

tests.name: dict-unset-1.2
tests.script:
# Test: dict unset - nonexistent key (no error)
set d [dict create a 1 b 2]
puts [dict unset d nonexistent]
puts $d

tests.name: dict-update-1.0
tests.script:
# Test: dict update - basic
set d [dict create a 1 b 2]
dict update d a x b y {
    puts "x=$x y=$y"
    set x 10
    set y 20
}
puts $d

tests.name: dict-update-1.1
tests.script:
# Test: dict update - missing key
set d [dict create a 1]
dict update d a x missing y {
    puts "x=$x"
    puts [info exists y]
}
puts $d

tests.name: dict-update-1.2
dict-update-1.3
dict-values-1.0
tests.script:
# Test: dict values - basic
set d [dict create a 1 b 2 c 3]
puts [dict values $d]

tests.name: dict-values-1.1
tests.script:
# Test: dict values - with pattern
set d [dict create a apple b banana c cherry]
puts [dict values $d]
puts [dict values $d a*]
puts [dict values $d *a*]
tests.stdout:
apple banana cherry
apple
apple banana

tests.name: dict-with-1.0
tests.script:
# Test: dict with - basic
set d [dict create a 1 b 2 c 3]
dict with d {
    puts "a=$a b=$b c=$c"
    set a 10
}
puts $d

tests.name: dict-with-1.1
tests.script:
# Test: dict with - nested path
set d [dict create outer [dict create x 1 y 2]]
dict with d outer {
    puts "x=$x y=$y"
    set x 10
}
puts [dict get $d outer x]

tests.name: dict-with-1.2
dict-with-1.3
dict-with-1.4
